/AQP6S5z6Ky-4Eswfl1trTDwqTNInMl1Ttzhl3LUlX4N-6v3tabWD0Xx9sMGO1FXbGUUzcO5a_z5cVNepD6tEbIbJ3PoXJDsSsgcxGQ0.mp4?_nc_cat=110&_nc_sid=9ca052&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_ohc=QKGGZfi4BI8Q7kNvwHz1PR1&%3D&ccb=17-1&_nc_gid=NOOWQK_jMkhjI2_r2pOCKA&_nc_zt=28&_nc_ss=7a32e&oh=00_Af2_HbTdz-_mMubbVEy0iHR4rlhQ7P2l2qKMoHeDye2ZfQ&oe=69D4B603", "manifest_stream_number": 0, "is_dash_periods": true, "protocol": "https", "video_ext": "mp4", "audio_ext": "none", "abr": 0, "vbr": 51.238, "resolution": "1080x1920", "aspect_ratio": 0.56, "filesize_approx": 396466, "http_headers": {"User-Agent": "Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/143.0.0.0 Safari/537.36", "Accept": "text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,*/*;q=0.8", "Accept-Language": "en-us,en;q=0.5", "Sec-Fetch-Mode": "navigate", "Referer": "https://www.instagram.com/"}, "format": "dash-820988014344278v - 1080x1920 (DASH video)"}], "title": "Video by sheturnedsavage", "description": "No one talks about this part.\n\nWhen pain has been your shadow for years,\nit stops feeling like something you carry —\nand starts feeling like who you are.\n\nYou’ve built yourself around it.\nLearned how to function with it.\nLearned how to explain yourself through it.\n\nThe sadness became your language.\nThe anxiety became your rhythm.\nThe grief became your identity.\n\nSo when someone says, “You’re healing,”\ninstead of relief… there’s fear.\n\nWho am I without the ache?\nWho am I without the story that shaped me?\nWho am I without the battles that carved themselves into my bones?\n\nHealing sounds beautiful in theory.\nBut in reality?\nIt feels like walking into a quiet room after years of chaos.\n\nAnd the quiet is unfamiliar.\nThe quiet is uncomfortable.\nThe quiet asks you to meet yourself without the armor.\n\nYou are not strange for being scared of that.\nYou are not weak for hesitating at the edge of peace.\n\nWhen pain has been your compass,\nletting it go can feel like losing direction.\n\nBut here’s the truth:\n\nYou are not your suffering.\nYou are not the worst thing that happened to you.\nYou are not the grief that shaped you.\n\nYou are the person who survived it.\n\nAnd the version of you that exists beyond the pain?\nShe isn’t empty.\nShe isn’t lost.\nShe isn’t unrecognisable.\n\nShe’s softer.\nStronger.\nQuieter in the best way.\n\nIt’s okay to be scared of meeting her.\n\nJust don’t run from her.\n\n🕊️ Follow @sheturnedsavage for grief quotes that hold your heart while you learn who you are outside the hurt.\n\n💬 If you’re struggling with your mental health and navigating healing feels overwhelming,\ncomment or DM “workbook.”\nYou don’t have to figure this out alone.\n\n#HealingIsScary\n#GriefJourney\n#IdentityAfterLoss\n#MentalHealthHealing\n#BecomingAfterBreakdown\n\nfear of healing, identity after trauma, grief and self discovery, healing anxiety support, emotional growth after loss, who am I without my pain, trauma identity shift, mental health recovery journey, learning to live without grief, healing feels unfamiliar, coping with long term sadness, emotional transformation process, overcoming fear of change, grief and personal growth, becoming after trauma\n\nDisclaimer; no copyright intended 🤍", "duration": 61.902, "timestamp": 1771371900, "uploader_id": "74856251976", "uploader": "Sar | Grief & Healing Quotes 🕊️", "channel": "sheturnedsavage", "like_count": 53981, "comment_count": 317, "comments": [{"author": "mehmedcetrefli", "author_id": "49305691497", "id": "18262485544293880", "text": "", "timestamp": 1775151827}, {"author": "dionne_pionne", "author_id": "3409015124", "id": "18111943216700544", "text": "@kristelmelissa.nl", "timestamp": 1775149311}, {"author": "dionne_pionne", "author_id": "3409015124", "id": "17925534426091872", "text": "Wow, I’ve felt this for so long, along with the longing to return to myself as the victim. I always found that so strange. How can you long for pain, sorrow, trauma? But you explain it well. Thank you.", "timestamp": 1775148185}, {"author": "anaofthemosthigh", "author_id": "72324674237", "id": "17922792075272268", "text": "I wrote almost the exact same thing I'm hearing, but mine said healing is weird", "timestamp": 1775125964}, {"author": "maelstrom374", "author_id": "80088029887", "id": "18360150169228967", "text": "Chalk outlines Ren", "timestamp": 1775120354}, {"author": "stellar888666", "author_id": "78101857183", "id": "17860140582567545", "text": "😢", "timestamp": 1775097366}, {"author": "gracelynn_howard", "author_id": "75343278422", "id": "18101812468936674", "text": "This is SO hard to overcome, but it IS possible. You just have to keep pushing toward that goal. I’ve been there before and it is terrible and really tough. But this “you” that you are scared of becoming is the best you there is. Think of that little girl inside of you, what would she want for you? You’ve got this! Don’t be scared to heal! Once you heal all the way you’ll look back and be so proud of yourself for coming so far. You CAN do this! Don’t be afraid to become the best version of yourself. You’ve got this because God’s got you. Keep pushing and don’t give up", "timestamp": 1775095285}, {"author": "noemi_privvvvv0", "author_id": "72828644080", "id": "18215162965316783", "text": "Io prima ora mi sorprendo come c'è l'abbia fatta", "timestamp": 1775067218}], "thumbnails": [{"url": "https://scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com/v/t51.82787-15/639935249_17877931773491977_3651349390872546567_n.jpg?stp=dst-jpg_e15_p640x640_tt6&efg=eyJ2ZW5jb2RlX3RhZyI6ImltYWdlX3VybGdlbi43MjB4MTI4MC5zZHIuZjgyNzg3LmRlZmF1bHRfY292ZXJfZnJhbWUuYzIifQ&_nc_ht=scontent-yyz1-1.cdninstagram.com&_nc_cat=101&_nc_oc=Q6cZ2gGerea4LQ7FzOlbw1DmgZJIpqvnwXaJ_qFT5AyeyAkF8_Qd1sEASH828h6qVue5f90&_nc_ohc=uLk6u8JPxrEQ7kNvwFhHymV&_nc_gid=NOOWQK_jMkhjI2_r2pOCKA&edm=ANTKIIoBAAAA&ccb=7-5&oh=00_Af2lyQ4y_hM2LFGMCYrbMP-u-tU9DUyb4DM8NAHeRry42A&oe=69D4C667&_nc_sid=d885a2", "width": 640, "height": 1137, "id": "0"